    <text>
        <body>
           <div type="edition" subtype="ogham" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="pgl-Ogam" resp="#POC">
            <ab> 
                <lb n="1" style="text-direction:up-down"/><persName><name nymRef="#?">ᚇᚏᚒ<unclear reason="damage">ᚌ</unclear><supplied reason="lost">ᚅᚑ</supplied></name> <w type="formula" lemma="maqqas"><unclear reason="damage">ᚋᚐ</unclear>ᚊ<supplied reason="lost">ᚔ</supplied></w> <w type="formula" lemma="muccoviias">ᚋ<supplied reason="lost">ᚒ</supplied><unclear reason="damage">ᚉ</unclear>ᚑ<unclear reason="damage">ᚔ</unclear></w> <name nymRef="#?"><gap extent="unknown" reason="lost"/><unclear reason="damage">ᚅ</unclear>ᚐᚋ<unclear reason="damage">ᚔ</unclear></name></persName>
            </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="edition" subtype="transliteration" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="pgl-Ogam" resp="#POC">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1" style="text-direction:up-down"/><persName><name nymRef="#?">DRU<unclear reason="damage">G</unclear><supplied reason="lost">NO</supplied></name> <w type="formula" lemma="maqqas"><unclear reason="damage">MA</unclear>Q<supplied reason="lost">I</supplied></w> <w type="formula" lemma="muccoviias">M<supplied reason="lost">U</supplied><unclear reason="damage">C</unclear>O<unclear reason="damage">I</unclear></w> <name nymRef="#?"><gap extent="unknown" reason="lost"/><unclear reason="damage">N</unclear>AM<unclear reason="damage">I</unclear></name></persName>
                </ab>
                <ab type="list">DRUG[NO] MAQ[I] M[U]COI [---]NAMI</ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app n="1">
                        <note>Macalister (1945, 36) noted that the letters DRU are quite clear and an uncut bar of rock on the edge interrupts the G score awkwardly. The N is worn nearly smooth by cattle rubbing. O and MA are traceable but also indistinct due to cattle rubbing. A hard projecting boss of stone on the edge interrupts the inscription at this point but the following QI is quite clear. The M at the top of the stone is just traceable but the U is gone. COI is clear at the top of the right angle. Of the ending to the final name NAMI only the AM is certain.</note>
                    </app>

                </listApp>               
            </div>
            <div type="translation">
                <p>'of Drón son of the descendant of...'</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>The inscription seems to consist of the MAQI MUCOI ('son of the kindred of') formula. Macalister (Pilsworth and Macalister 1940, 93) suggested that <q>the name DRUGNO is identical with that of the family of <persName xml:lang="sga">Uí Dróna</persName>, whose territory (the Carlow baronies of Idrone) extend to within seven miles of the site of the stone</q> (see also (McManus 1991, 179, n.34). This name is also found in inscription I-KER-035 (CIIC 167): DROGNO (Ballyandreen, Co. Kerry) and also possibly in I-KER-033 (CIIC 165): [D]ROGNO (Ballintermon, Co. Kerry). </p>
                    
            </div>
